Biomass Conversion - The Interface of Biotechnology, Chemistry and Materials Science (Springer, 2012).pdf

ISBN 978-3-642-28417-5

Given that humans must give up fossil fuels the ecological equivalent of a self-destructive addiction alternatives are urgently needed. This book covers state-of-the-art methods of biomass conversion that may go some way to plugging the energy gap
